# Network Scanner

A command-line tool to scan your local network, discover connected devices, check network health, and identify device types.

## Features

- **Network Discovery**: Automatically finds all devices on your local network using ARP scanning
- **Device Identification**: Identifies device types based on MAC address vendor, open ports, and hostname
- **Network Health Monitoring**: Checks latency and packet loss for all devices
- **Custom Device Labeling**: Add persistent labels to devices for easier identification
- **Port Scanning**: Optional port scanning to help identify device types (requires nmap)